@Elias: Did you note that Matias was not the only one to make that mountain into a molehill? If not why not if it is scummy to you?<br>
<br>
@triangle and DCL: <br>
Stop attacking each other for a moment and give your views on everyone in the game thus far.

@farside<br>
I usually play that way when I'm a PR, actually. I'm scared the scum will kill me.<br>
I'm not sure what prae's meta with this stuff is.

@ TheFool &amp; Praetyre, Are you guys able to talk with the people you neighborized during the day?<br>
<br>
@Praetyre, can you tell us who you neighborized?<br>
<br>
@Captain, can you confirm that TheFool neighborized you?

@redFF: That could be your lynch then. You think it's still a good idea?<br>
How far are you will to state 1/3 and say for sure one is scum. I love WIFOM, mod gaming and such it's part of mafia. All I know is that Gerturde flipped tracker and 3 people claimed neighbors. Neighbors are really, really weak roles in a game. There is no confirmation, the role is only to talk with a player for one game day. <br>
If push came to shove I would say Prae is my top scum suspects with all the neighbor claims but I want to look outside those neighbors, see what others have to say. There is nothing wrong with talking about scum suspects here.

@farside I've already explained it, look at post 351. But since you didn't seem to have read that here is the short version:<br>
<br>
I don't see any reason a scum neighborizer would claim neighborizer after a town claim. If I was a scum neighborizer and the town one had been outed day 1, I would just neighborize a scumbuddy and get daychat with them. Which would be the best way to go as scum. This is why I see TF, and redFF's claims to be town, and prae's to be scum.

Is everybody really so against lynching a neighborizer? Red had nothing to back up his suspicion from yesterday, whatever. But other lynches being bad yesterday is no excuse for saying "triangle is the lynch" today. If he were town he would've expanded your reasoning when I questioned it, not pointed back to vague indications of a scum read. And at your first opportunity, not after repeated questioning from both me and Farside.<br>
<div align="center"><hr style="height:14px;width:100%"></div><br>
@Matias - Well first, I'm not saying OMGUS is a scumtell. I am saying it somewhat delegitimizes a lot of attacks in my eyes. That being said, I do see where you're coming from with IS. His contribution has been lacking and his attacks on you are pretty poor. I wouldn't say I'm very convinced he's scum, because he's done the same to me and flipped town. What concerns me more is his apparent lack of views on the majority of things going on in the game. Not to mention his lack of views on the majority of players. But then again IS is a lurker and thread-skimmer by trade. Certainly a wagon could do him a world of good, but RedFF is so incredibly obvious here that he'll just have to wait.<br>
<div align="center"><hr style="height:14px;width:100%"></div><br>
@Farside - Why would I ask Triangle to explain a town read that I shared with him? I was more focused on Praetyre's attackers and making a case for a scooby lynch. <br>
<div align="center"><hr style="height:14px;width:100%"></div><br>
@IS - Do you really think that Matias is more scummy than Red, who has no clue why he's been suspecting someone for the entire game?

@matias, I want to see that compilation of how gertrude suspected gorckat.<br>
<br>
I honestly don't see the purpose to analyzing the gertrude nk, seems like there is too much wifom involved.

@redFF<br>
<br>
don't lay down a vote for a third person. Town will lose for sure if that happens. If three separate people get voted for, at least one of them is town voting for town. Which means that scum will for sure be able to quick-hammer someone.

@IS where exactly am I "pleading"?<br>
<br>
care to quote that part?
